	<TD WIDTH="20%"><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="2" COLOR="#333399">Author</FONT></TD>
	<TD><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="2"COLOR="#333399">Samita's Guide to Oasis Spec's</FONT></TD>
</TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#f7f5e6" ALIGN="LEFT">
<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#333399"><b>Flaim</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399"><B>Natures Chosen</B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Joined: Jun 13, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posts: 352</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">From: Kelethin<br></FONT></td><TD valign="top"><img src="/boards/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posted: 2001-06-14 01:17&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">Important things to note:<BR><BR>There are 8, 8, 8 spectres there<BR><BR>1...........2<BR>........3<BR>.......456<BR>7.....x....8<BR><BR>Where 3 4 and 6 are in the top of the tower<BR><BR>You can succesfully pull singles when there is a partial spawn, but I don't risk it - ever - harmony is your friend<BR><BR>What I do is stand at spot x in wolf form and levitated - just up over the edge - nothing will agro from here - they have amazingly small agro ranges if they are not attacked.<BR><BR>I use the F9x2 (from behind) view pulled all the way back, select 1 and harmony - sit(med) - stand - 2 harmony - 5 harmony - (7 or 8) harmony - Pull the last one you have not harmonied - away from the island and kite away - ALWAYS harmony number 5 - HE will come if you are pulling 2 or 8 and usually 1 or 7 as well depending on your skill. I also do not snare them for the pull. 2 reasons - I want it far away fast to avoid being spawned on. And I hate waiting for it on the shore. I cast snare as it comes out of the water - works well for me.<BR><BR>Keep using the from behind view and make sure you stay within range of the spectre - DONOT out run it or it may stop off and attack anyone it sees nearby - THIS IS IMPORTANT - try not to make an a$$ of yourself buy being a newbie menace - I have only made 2 bad pulls from spectre island - they were my first 2 pulls....<BR><BR>Anyway - go back to the island the second you are done and meditate in spot x. monitor the island for spawns and pulls and keep track of other peoples pulls so you know the spawn order. <BR><BR>What do you do when there are others there and you need to pull from the tower and the 5 at the base are gone?<BR>IT gets harder - move to the corner my the ramp on the right side of the door - push your nose all the way into the corner - select yourself and harmony. This will get the ones on the top. Try and select number 3 and pull him out. For some reason number 3 can avoid the harmony so if you pull 4 or 6 you might get a 2 spectre pull. luckily when I learned this I was grouped and we killed them handily.<BR><BR>Another neat trick is harmony 5 (by harmonying #5 the top 3 get the harmony too) and pull from the top - leaving the one in the base of the tower. Why? If you break up the top smartly then some idiot doesnt come along and pull all 3 and train the newbies and get you stomped when they float back after they zone to safety.<BR><BR>IF things get busy at spectre tower - 3 groups/solo - start finding the leaders and work a pull system. usually first representative back to the island is next to pull. yes groups will get more, but then again a typical solo druid (34/44) can kill from 2 to 4 in the 17 minute spawn series (depends on level). Even offer to harmony for them if they dont have a druid or ranger. Makes things safer for everyone. <BR><BR>What do you do if a jerk comes by?<BR>Group with the people you have been sharing with and out blast the single jerk. You tend to like the fact you can stop the specs so fast you get more overall kills - with 3 decent casters you can stay on spectre island - along the slope to the water and have very little wasted time pulling.<BR><BR>What to do if it gets downright slow due to over camping?<BR>If you are solo - dealwith it or leave. Pull your 1 when you can without being too greedy.<BR>IF you have build that group as above, go pull DW gobs to fill the downtime. Yes they are harder. But if you were going to do nothing for 10 minutes anyway why not fight them.<BR><BR>In wolf form they do not agro - just harmony 3 of the corners and pull the 4th - there is one in the tower but he does not agro (gets harmonied or just stays put) - be ready to HEAL when fighting wizzies.<BR><BR>Samita Littlethorn lvl 44 Solusek Ro<BR><BR><BR><BR><BR>.........z...<BR>.y......3<BR>.......4.6<BR>..........x.<BR><BR>Here is how I do it:<BR>A) KNOW for a fact that the bottom 5 are not spawning soon<BR>B) move to position x - nose stuck in the corner at the end of the ramp against the tower<BR>C) Select self and cast harmony - this ALWAYS harmonies 4 and 6 and only sometimes gets 3<BR>D) move to position y and get the select on spectre number 3<BR>E) snare or blast - I blast to pull him away fast<BR>F) run him northish<BR><BR>- or you could, but I don't like hanging out on the platform too long -<BR>D) move to position z against the tower<BR>E) cast harmony again<BR>F) select a spectre and pull<BR><BR>Good luck - I hope this helps <BR>Samita Littlethorn lvl 44 Solusek Ro<BR><BR><BR><BR><font size=-1>[ This Message was edited by: Flaim on 2001-06-14 01:18 ]</font></FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#f7f5e6"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=221"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Flaim"></a>
