<TD valign=top><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" COLOR="#333399"><b>Iglacias</b></FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399"><B>Nature lover</B></font><BR><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Joined: Jun 12, 2001</FONT><br><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posts: 34</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">From: USA<br></FONT></td><TD valign="top"><img src="/boards/images/posticon.gif"><FONT FACE="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica" SIZE="1" COLOR="#333399">Posted: 2001-06-14 03:41&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp<HR></font>

<FONT COLOR="#333399" face="Trebuchet MS, Arial, Helvetica">At level 45 I quad kited specs via the advice of a mage friend of mine.  I had never considering quadding them before, but it worked great.  got nearly a whole blue per quad in lvl 45, and they weren't that hard..  its almost impossible to pull MORE than 4 at once unless you TRY, so its relatively safe.  the only trick is lining them up without letting them get close enuf to cast their lifetap -- as the brief casting time makes them stop for a second and get out of group.  Once you know how to line them up, just run completely out of range of AE and press it repeatedly till it casts..  Not too hard, just stay as far away as you can <IMG SRC="/boards/images/smiles/icon_smile.gif">   it's a blast taking out the menaces 4 at once, i'll tell ya..<BR>_________________________________<BR>[52 Wanderer] Iglacias (Halfling)<BR><BR><BR><font size=-1>[ This Message was edited by: Iglacias on 2001-06-14 03:43 ]</font></FONT><BR></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR="#e6ebd7"><TD nowrap align="left">&nbsp;</TD><TD><table border="1" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" width="100%"><tr><td>&nbsp;&nbsp<a href="/boards/bb_profile.php?mode=view&user=110"><img src="/boards/images/profile.gif" border=0 alt="View Profile of Iglacias"></a>
